ğŸ”· CSS FLEXBOX (One-Dimensional Layout)

Flexbox is used to align items in **one direction** (row OR column).

---

ğŸ§± Flex Container

```css
.container {
  display: flex;
}
```

---

â¡ï¸ Flex Direction

```css
flex-direction: row;        /* default */
flex-direction: column;
```

---

ğŸ“ Justify Content (Horizontal Alignment)

```css
justify-content: center;
justify-content: space-between;
justify-content: space-around;
justify-content: space-evenly;
```

---

ğŸ“ Align Items (Vertical Alignment)

```css
align-items: center;
align-items: flex-start;
align-items: flex-end;
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Flex Wrap

```css
flex-wrap: wrap;
```

---

ğŸ“¦ Flex Item Properties

```css
.item {
  flex-grow: 1;
  flex-shrink: 1;
  flex-basis: 200px;
}
```

Shortcut:

```css
flex: 1 1 200px;
```

---

âœ… Flexbox Use Cases

* Navbar
* Cards layout
* Centering elements
* Simple responsive layouts

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ”· CSS GRID (Two-Dimensional Layout)

Grid is used to design layouts in **rows AND columns**.

---

ğŸ§± Grid Container

```css
.container {
  display: grid;
}
```

---

ğŸ“ Define Columns & Rows

```css
grid-template-columns: 1fr 1fr 1fr;
grid-template-rows: auto;
```

---

ğŸ“ Gap Between Items

```css
gap: 20px;
```

---

ğŸ“¦ Grid Item Placement

```css
.item {
  grid-column: 1 / 3;
  grid-row: 1 / 2;
}
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ” Auto Layout

```css
grid-template-columns: repeat(3, 1fr);
```

---

âœ… Grid Use Cases

* Full website layout
* Dashboards
* Complex responsive designs

---

ğŸ†š Flexbox vs Grid

| Flexbox       | Grid            |
| ------------- | --------------- |
| 1D layout     | 2D layout       |
| Content-based | Layout-based    |
| Simple UI     | Complex layouts |

ğŸ“Œ **Flexbox + Grid together = real-world websites**

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“ CSS POSITIONING

Types of Positioning

```css
position: static;   /* default */
position: relative;
position: absolute;
position: fixed;
position: sticky;
```

Examples

```css
.box {
  position: absolute;
  top: 20px;
  left: 10px;
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ“± RESPONSIVE DESIGN (Very Important)

Media Queries

```css
@media (max-width: 768px) {
  body {
    background-color: lightgray;
  }
}
```

ğŸ“Œ Makes website work on:

* Mobile
* Tablet
* Desktop

---

ğŸ¯ CSS Z-INDEX

Controls **layer order**.

```css
.box {
  position: relative;
  z-index: 10;
}
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸŒˆ CSS TRANSITIONS

Smooth animations.

```css
button {
  transition: background 0.3s ease;
}
```

---------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸï¸ CSS TRANSFORMS

```css
transform: rotate(10deg);
transform: scale(1.2);
transform: translateX(20px);
```

-----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ¬ CSS ANIMATIONS

```css
@keyframes move {
  from { left: 0; }
  to { left: 100px; }
}

.box {
  animation: move 2s infinite;
}
```

-------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§  CSS VARIABLES

Reusable values.

```css
:root {
  --main-color: blue;
}

h1 {
  color: var(--main-color);
}
```

----------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ§© CSS OVERFLOW

```css
overflow: hidden;
overflow: scroll;
overflow: auto;
```

---

ğŸ–±ï¸ CSS PSEUDO-CLASSES

```css
a:hover {
  color: red;
}
```

Common:

* `:hover`
* `:active`
* `:focus`
* `:nth-child()`

---

ğŸ§¾ CSS PSEUDO-ELEMENTS

```css
p::first-letter {
  font-size: 30px;
}
```

Common:

* `::before`
* `::after`
* `::first-letter`

------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

âŒ Common CSS Advanced Mistakes

* Overusing `!important.`
* Not using responsive units
* Ignoring mobile-first design
* Mixing Flexbox & Grid incorrectly

--------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------------

ğŸ’¡ Best Practices (Advanced CSS)

* Use Flexbox & Grid together
* Follow a mobile-first approach
* Use CSS variables
* Keep CSS modular
* Avoid inline CSS

